enhanced_by.reason: The wrap method is the inverse operation of unwrap, as it wraps elements with HTML, while unwrap removes the parent elements.
The empty method removes all child nodes from each matched element, which might be a necessary step before unwrapping to ensure no child nodes are left behind.
The html method retrieves the combined inner HTML of all matched elements, which can be used to assert the state of the DOM after unwrapping.
The text method retrieves the combined text of all matched elements, which can be used to assert the text content after unwrapping.
